build for web

# Product Landing Page -- multi-page marketing site with hero, features, and pricing

# Uses built-in page presets: page_hero, page_section, page_section_dark, page_card
# Override any preset by redefining it here. These are the defaults.

# --- Home Page ---

page 'Clear' at '/':

  section 'Hero' with style page_hero:
    small text 'Business Apps, Built By AI'
    heading 'Your app is already built. Just tell us what to change.'
    text 'Clear comes with production-ready business apps -- invoicing, project management, CRM, ecommerce, and more. Describe what makes yours different. We handle the rest.'
    divider
    link 'See the Apps' to '/apps'
    link 'How It Works' to '/how'
    link 'Why Not Lovable' to '/compare'

  section 'Problem' with style page_section:
    heading 'You Do Not Need An App Built From Scratch'
    text 'Every invoice system has invoices. Every project tracker has tasks. Every CRM has contacts. You are not unique in what you need -- you are unique in how you need it.'
    divider
    text 'Other AI app builders start from zero every time. "Build me an invoice system" generates 2,000 lines of code from scratch, with all the bugs that come from writing something for the first time.'
    text 'Clear starts from a tested, deployed invoice system that already works. You say "add a 30-day payment term" or "require manager approval over $5,000" and we modify the one that already passes 27 automated tests.'
    divider
    bold text 'Starting from working is faster than starting from zero.'

  section 'Apps' with style page_section_dark:
    heading 'Apps Ready Today'
    text 'Each app is deployed, tested, and ready to customize. Pick one and make it yours.'
    divider
    subheading 'Invoicing'
    text 'Clients, invoices, line items, payments. Status tracking: draft, sent, paid, cancelled. Role-based access. Admin audit log. 27 automated tests passing.'
    divider
    subheading 'Project Management'
    text 'Teams, members, projects, tasks, comments. Priority levels, assignment, hour tracking. Sidebar layout with live data. 36 automated tests passing.'
    divider
    subheading 'Ecommerce'
    text 'Product catalog, orders, inventory guards. Stripe checkout. Webhook verification. Stock management. 16 automated tests passing.'
    divider
    subheading 'Customer Portal'
    text 'User accounts, support tickets, knowledge base. Auth with roles. Email notifications. Rate limiting on public endpoints.'
    divider
    subheading 'Team Chat'
    text 'Rooms, messages, real-time updates. User presence. Message history. Auth required for posting.'
    divider
    subheading 'Job Queue'
    text 'Background tasks with scheduling. Status tracking, retry logic. Admin dashboard. Role-based access.'
    divider
    subheading 'And More'
    text 'URL shortener. Blog with admin panel. SaaS billing. Webhook relay. Live metrics dashboard. Or describe something new -- Clear builds it from scratch too.'

  section 'Customize' with style page_section:
    heading 'Make It Yours In Plain English'
    text 'You do not write code. You describe changes.'
    divider
    subheading 'Add a business rule'
    italic text '"Invoices over $10,000 need director approval before sending."'
    text 'Clear adds the rule, the validation, the role check, and the test. One sentence from you.'
    divider
    subheading 'Change a workflow'
    italic text '"Orders should go through a review step before fulfillment."'
    text 'Clear adds the status, the transition guard, and updates the test suite.'
    divider
    subheading 'Add a field'
    italic text '"I need a purchase order number on every invoice."'
    text 'Clear adds the field to the database, the form, the API validation, and the display.'
    divider
    subheading 'Tweak the UI'
    italic text '"Put the sidebar on the right and add a search bar at the top."'
    text 'Clear regenerates the layout. Same data, same logic, new arrangement.'

  section 'Trust' with style page_section_dark:
    heading 'You Can Read Every Line'
    text 'This is what your invoice app actually looks like under the hood:'
    divider
    code block 'when user calls PUT /api/invoices/:id/send:\n  requires auth\n  define invoice as: look up the Invoice with this id\n  guard invoice is not nothing or "Invoice not found"\n  guard invoice`s status is "draft" or "Only drafts can be sent"\n  invoice`s status is "sent"\n  save invoice to Invoices\n  send back "sent" with success message'
    divider
    text 'Eight lines. You can read every one. "Require login, find the invoice, check it is a draft, change the status, save it." No React hooks. No middleware chains. No mysteries.'
    text 'You will probably never need to read this. But knowing you can is the difference between renting your software and owning it.'

  section 'Security' with style page_section:
    heading 'Security You Do Not Have To Think About'
    text 'Every app we ship has security built into the compiler. Not checked after the fact -- enforced before your app can run.'
    divider
    bold text 'No delete endpoint works without login. Ever.'
    text 'The compiler blocks it. It is not a setting you can forget to turn on.'
    bold text 'No API returns another user`s private data.'
    text 'The compiler detects it and refuses to build.'
    bold text 'Every form input is validated.'
    text 'Required fields, length limits, email format, type checks -- all generated from your data model.'
    bold text 'Every app has automated tests.'
    text 'Auth, validation, error handling, edge cases -- tested before you ever see it.'

  section 'Compare' with style page_section_dark:
    heading 'Why Not Just Use Lovable?'
    text 'Lovable is impressive. So are Bolt and v0. But they all have the same problem.'
    divider
    bold text 'They start from scratch every time.'
    text 'Your invoice app is generated fresh. Every bug is a new bug. Every security hole is a new security hole. Nothing is tested until you find the problem.'
    divider
    bold text 'They generate code you cannot read.'
    text '2,400 lines of React and TypeScript. When it breaks, you ask the AI to fix it and hope. When you want a small change, you ask the AI to change it and hope.'
    divider
    bold text 'They lock you into their platform.'
    text 'Supabase for data. Vercel for hosting. Their editor for changes. Leave and you take a pile of generated React with you.'
    divider
    subheading 'Clear is different.'
    text 'Your app starts from one that already works and already has tests. Changes are described in English, applied to a readable blueprint, verified by automated tests. Export your app and host it anywhere -- standard Node.js, no vendor lock-in.'

  section 'Pricing' with style page_section:
    heading 'Pricing'
    divider
    subheading 'Starter -- Free'
    text 'One app. Hosted by Clear. Custom domain. Community support.'
    divider
    subheading 'Business -- $49/month'
    text 'Unlimited apps. Priority support. Custom integrations. Export source code anytime.'
    divider
    subheading 'Enterprise -- Contact Us'
    text 'On-premise deployment. SSO. Audit logging. Dedicated support. SLA.'
    divider
    small text 'All plans include: automated tests, security enforcement, daily backups, SSL.'

  section 'CTA' with style page_hero:
    heading 'Your app is already built.'
    text 'Pick a template. Describe your changes. Ship today.'
    link 'See the Apps' to '/apps'

# --- Apps Catalog Page ---

page 'Apps' at '/apps':

  section 'CatalogHero' with style page_hero:
    heading 'Pick Your Starting Point'
    text 'Every app below is deployed, tested, and ready to customize. Click to see the blueprint.'

  section 'Catalog' with style page_section:
    subheading 'Invoicing System'
    text '5 tables: Clients, Invoices, Line Items, Payments, Audit Log. Status machine with guards. Role-based access. 27 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: freelancers, agencies, small businesses that outgrew spreadsheet invoicing.'
    divider
    subheading 'Project Manager'
    text '6 tables: Teams, Members, Projects, Tasks, Comments, Activity. Priority tracking, assignment, hour estimates. Sidebar layout. 36 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: teams that need something simpler than Jira but more structured than a shared doc.'
    divider
    subheading 'Ecommerce Backend'
    text 'Products, orders, inventory guards. Stripe checkout. Webhook signature verification. Admin-only product management. 16 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: shops, marketplaces, any business selling products online.'
    divider
    subheading 'Blog with Admin'
    text 'Posts, users, roles. Public reading, authenticated writing. Admin-only user management. Email validation. 14 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: content marketing, company blogs, knowledge bases.'
    divider
    subheading 'Team Chat'
    text 'Rooms, messages, real-time delivery. Auth for posting. Message history per room. 12 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: internal communication, customer support chat, community forums.'
    divider
    subheading 'SaaS Billing'
    text 'Subscription plans, usage tracking, tier limits. Webhook for payment events. 6 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: any SaaS product that needs subscription management.'
    divider
    subheading 'URL Shortener'
    text 'Short links with hit counting. Rate limiting. Unique code generation. 7 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: marketing teams, link tracking, branded short URLs.'
    divider
    subheading 'Live Dashboard'
    text 'Real-time metrics via server-sent events. Data aggregation jobs. REST API for posting metrics. 8 tests.'
    italic text 'Good for: ops teams, monitoring, KPI dashboards.'
    divider
    subheading 'Something Else?'
    text 'Describe what you need. If it has a database, an API, and a user interface, Clear can build it. Most custom apps are ready in minutes, not weeks.'

  section 'CatalogCTA' with style page_hero:
    heading 'Pick one and make it yours.'
    link 'Back to Home' to '/'

# --- How It Works Page ---

page 'How It Works' at '/how':

  section 'HowHero' with style page_hero:
    heading 'Three Steps to Your App'
    text 'No coding. No waiting. Full ownership.'

  section 'Pick' with style page_section:
    heading 'Step 1: Pick a Template'
    text 'Browse the app catalog. Find the closest match to what you need. Every template is a real, tested, deployed application -- not a wireframe or a mockup.'
    text 'The invoice system already handles clients, invoices, line items, payments, and status tracking. If that is 80% of what you need, start there.'

  section 'Describe' with style page_section_dark:
    heading 'Step 2: Describe Your Changes'
    text 'Tell Clear how your business is different. Use plain English.'
    divider
    italic text '"Add a purchase order field to invoices. Make it required. Show it in the table."'
    italic text '"Add a discount field. If the invoice total is over $5,000, allow up to 15% discount."'
    italic text '"Add an export button that generates a PDF of the invoice."'
    divider
    text 'Clear updates the blueprint, the database, the API, the validation, the forms, and the tests. You verify the changes in the readable blueprint and approve.'

  section 'Ship' with style page_section:
    heading 'Step 3: Ship'
    text 'Your app is compiled, tested, and deployed. You get a URL, a custom domain option, and a dashboard to manage your data.'
    text 'Every change runs through automated tests before it goes live. If a change breaks something, you see it before your users do.'
    divider
    bold text 'Average time from "I need this change" to live in production: under 5 minutes.'

  section 'Ongoing' with style page_section_dark:
    heading 'After Launch'
    text 'Your app keeps getting better without you doing anything.'
    divider
    bold text 'We improve the compiler weekly.'
    text 'Better error handling, faster performance, new security checks. Your app benefits automatically on the next deploy.'
    bold text 'You own the blueprint.'
    text 'Export it anytime. It is 37-250 lines of readable text. Take it to any developer, any platform, any host. No lock-in.'
    bold text 'Support that understands your app.'
    text 'Because we can read your blueprint, our support team knows exactly what your app does. No "send us your codebase" -- we already see it.'

  section 'HowCTA' with style page_hero:
    heading 'Five minutes to your first app.'
    link 'See the Apps' to '/apps'
    link 'Back to Home' to '/'

# --- Compare Page ---

page 'Compare' at '/compare':

  section 'CompareHero' with style page_hero:
    heading 'Clear vs Other AI App Builders'
    text 'Honest comparison. You decide.'

  section 'VsLovable' with style page_section:
    heading 'Clear vs Lovable'
    divider
    bold text 'Lovable: starts from scratch every time.'
    text 'You describe an invoice system. Lovable generates 2,400 lines of React, Tailwind, Supabase, and TypeScript. Fresh code, untested, with whatever bugs this particular generation happens to have.'
    divider
    bold text 'Clear: starts from a tested invoice system.'
    text 'You pick the invoice template (27 automated tests already passing) and describe your customizations. Your app inherits months of battle-tested logic.'
    divider
    bold text 'When something breaks:'
    text 'Lovable: you ask the AI to fix it and wait. You cannot read the code to verify the fix.'
    text 'Clear: you read the blueprint (8 lines for the send-invoice endpoint), see the problem, describe the fix. Or just fix line 14 yourself.'

  section 'VsBolt' with style page_section_dark:
    heading 'Clear vs Bolt'
    divider
    bold text 'Bolt is fast. Clear is fast and tested.'
    text 'Bolt generates a full-stack app in seconds. Impressive. But it generates it fresh every time, with no tests, no security enforcement, and code you need a developer to maintain.'
    text 'Clear generates from tested templates with 6 to 36 automated tests per app. Security is enforced by the compiler. The readable blueprint means a non-developer can maintain it.'

  section 'VsV0' with style page_section:
    heading 'Clear vs v0'
    divider
    bold text 'v0 does frontend beautifully. Clear does everything.'
    text 'v0 generates React components. Beautiful ones. But you still need a backend, a database, auth, validation, deployment, and tests. That is 80% of the work.'
    text 'Clear generates the full stack from one description. Frontend, backend, database, auth, validation, tests, deployment. One tool, complete app.'

  section 'VsTraditional' with style page_section_dark:
    heading 'Clear vs Hiring a Developer'
    divider
    bold text 'A developer costs $10,000-50,000 for a custom business app.'
    text 'Timeline: 2-6 months. You get exactly what you asked for -- 3 months ago. Changes cost more time and money.'
    divider
    bold text 'Clear costs $49/month.'
    text 'Timeline: today. Changes take 5 minutes. And if you ever outgrow Clear, export your blueprint and hand it to a developer. They will understand it in 30 seconds.'

  section 'Table' with style page_section:
    heading 'Feature Comparison'
    divider
    bold text 'Starts from tested templates'
    text 'Clear: Yes. Lovable: No. Bolt: No. v0: No.'
    bold text 'Readable source code'
    text 'Clear: Yes (37-250 lines). Lovable: No (2,400+ lines). Bolt: No. v0: Frontend only.'
    bold text 'Automated tests included'
    text 'Clear: Yes (6-36 per app). Lovable: No. Bolt: No. v0: No.'
    bold text 'Security enforced at build time'
    text 'Clear: Yes (compiler blocks insecure code). Lovable: No. Bolt: No. v0: No.'
    bold text 'Full-stack (frontend + backend + database)'
    text 'Clear: Yes. Lovable: Yes. Bolt: Yes. v0: Frontend only.'
    bold text 'Export and self-host'
    text 'Clear: Yes (standard Node.js). Lovable: Partial (Supabase dependency). Bolt: Yes. v0: Yes (frontend only).'
    bold text 'Non-developer can make changes'
    text 'Clear: Yes (plain English or edit blueprint). Lovable: Ask the AI. Bolt: Ask the AI. v0: Ask the AI.'

  section 'CompareCTA' with style page_hero:
    heading 'Try it yourself. Pick an app and customize it.'
    link 'See the Apps' to '/apps'
    link 'Back to Home' to '/'
